oned in the SOW falls under our Boundary\"','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(140,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 16:59:03','669892','SC','CHARLESTON','Self QC',2,'','Magellan Tool','Boundary Placement','If our SOW involves working near to any Termination box (Business class) then our Boundary must cover all the LU\'s parcels been served by the respective tap by enabling parcel layer.\n\n Note : All Boundaries must be flushed & made sure turned off COAX/Fiber layers doesn\'t overlap the PCAB boundary.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(141,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 16:59:03','669892','SC','CHARLESTON','Self QC',2,'','Magellan Tool','Trace & Analyze','Ensure to Run the Trace from given MUX by selecting splice matrix TOOL in Inspector panel.\nCustomer connected Fibers must be trace back to Headend/hub.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(142,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 16:59:03','669892','SC','CHARLESTON','Self QC',2,'','Magellan Tool','Shape & Position of all elements','All Support & Fiber elements shape/positioning/rotation inside our PRISM PCAB boundary must match with provided Asbuilt input file & also follow standard Charter guidelines. \n\nIf there is a conflict between guideline & asbuilt reach out to your respective supervisor','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(143,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 16:59:03','669892','SC','CHARLESTON','Self QC',2,'','Magellan Tool','Manufacture types','All Fiber elements manufacturer types must match with regional specification document which is available on the MQMS Library.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(144,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 16:59:03','669892','SC','CHARLESTON','Self QC',2,'','Magellan Tool','Base Layers','Ensure 3 Base layers - Centre line, Parcel line and Street Names are enabled.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(145,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 16:59:03','669892','SC','CHARLESTON','Self QC',2,'','Magellan Tool','Scaling','Match the scaling of all devices in the area.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(146,'T