elengths in the MUX.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(840,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Naming Circuits & Sub circuits','Ensure the naming of Circuits and Sub-circuits as per the standards.\nCircuit naming format: BC-customer address without spaces \nSubcircuits naming format: BC-customer address without spaces_FWD/RTN','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(841,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','BUILD STATE','Asbuilt Jobs: The build state must be \"Asbuilt\" of all the address, support structures, Fiber(alos coax if hybrid) Elements updated or changed as per the SOW inside the respective PRSIM PCAB Boundary\nIt must be Always \"Asbuilt\" even added any new Elements of FIBER, Support and Addresses.  \n\nRestore Jobs: Built state Must be \"NOT BUILT\"','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(842,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Boundary Placement','Asbuilt Jobs: Existing PRISM ID Boundary type must be changed to \"PRSIM PCAB Boundary\" & renamed with JOB ID, thru inspector tool.  \n\nRestore Jobs: Existing PRISM ID Boundary type must be changed to \"NOT BUILT Boundary\" & renamed with JOB ID, thru inspector tool.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(843,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Boundary Placement','Asbuilt jobs: If existing PRISM ID Boundary not available in Magellan, then New  \"PRSIM PCAB Boundary\" must be placed according to the parcels in Magellan.\n\nRestore jobs: If existing PRISM ID Boundary not available in Magellan, then New \"NOT BUILT Boundary\" must be placed according to the parcels in Magellan.\nEnsure entire area mentioned in the SOW falls under our Boundary\"','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(844,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Boundary Placement','If our SOW involves working near to any Termination box (Business class) then our Boundary must cover all the LU\'s parcels been served by the respective tap by enabling parcel layer.\n\n Note : All Boundaries must be flushed & made sure turned off COAX/Fiber layers doesn\'t overlap the PCAB boundary.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(845,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Trace & Analyze','Ensure to Run the Trace from given MUX by selecting splice matrix TOOL in Inspector panel.\nCustomer connected Fibers must be trace back to Headend/hub.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(846,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Shape & Position of all elements','All Support & Fiber elements shape/positioning/rotation inside our PRISM PCAB boundary must match with provided Asbuilt input file & also follow standard Charter guidelines. \n\nIf there is a conflict between guideline & asbuilt reach out to your respective supervisor','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(847,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Manufacture types','All Fiber elements manufacturer types must match with regional specification document which is available on the MQMS Library.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(848,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Base Layers','Ensure 3 Base layers - Centre line, Parcel line and Street Names are enabled.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(849,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','Magellan Tool','Scaling','Match the scaling of all devices in the area.','Yes','','100.0','Ajith V'),(850,'Testing ATX AS-Built','2023-09-21 18:11:47','1605504','NC','KERNERSVILLE','IQC',1,'','After Deliverables','After Print extraction','Prints must be exported by ensuring the asbuilt area is in